<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n36091h"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36091h">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36091h"> 91(h)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> pinkindindies</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Many of these &ldquo;Bloods&rdquo; were known as &ldquo;sweaters&rdquo; and &ldquo;<mark>pinkindindies</mark>&rdquo;, the former practiced &ldquo;sweating,&rdquo; that is, forcing persons to deliver up their arms; the latter cut off a small portion from the ends of their scabbards, suffering the naked point of the sword to project; with these they prodded or &ldquo;pinked&rdquo; those unoffending passers-by on whom they thought fit to bestow their attentions. <small> Samuel A. Ossory Fitzpatrick, <a name="SAOF" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#SAOF"><cite title="source">Dublin: A Historical and Topographical Account of the City</cite></a> (1907) 205</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
